tvshowdetails.label: The Blacklist
tvshowdetails.plot:
Raymond "Red" Reddington, one of the FBI's most wanted fugitives, surrenders in person at FBI Headquarters in Washington, D.C. He claims that he and the FBI have the same interests: bringing down dangerous criminals and terrorists. In the last two decades, he's made a list of criminals and terrorists that matter the most but the FBI cannot find because it does not know they exist. Reddington calls this "The Blacklist".
Reddington will co-operate, but insists that he will speak only to Elizabeth Keen, a rookie FBI profiler.
tvshowdetails.title: The Blacklist

1.label: 1x01. Pilot
1.plot: A criminal mastermind surrenders to the FBI with a stunning offer - but he'll only talk to a rookie profiler.
1.title: Pilot

1.label: 1x02. The Freelancer
1.plot: Liz and Red track an assassin who disguises his kills in large-scale catastrophes.
1.title: The Freelancer

1.label: 1x03. Wujing
1.plot: Liz and Red go undercover to take down an assassin who's been decimating the ranks of the CIA.
1.title: Wujing

1.label: 1x04. The Stewmaker
1.plot: When Liz's key witness disappears, Red suspects a killer who literally stews his victims, making them disappear forever...
1.title: The Stewmaker

1.label: 1x05. The Courier
1.plot: A sinister middleman with a unique ability puts the FBI on the trail of a missing NSA analyst.
1.title: The Courier

1.label: 1x06. Gina Zanetakos
1.plot: Eager to clear Tom's name, Liz turns him in to the FBI.
1.title: Gina Zanetakos

1.label: 1x07. Frederick Barnes
1.plot: Following a chemical attack on the subway, Liz and the team hunt a mad scientist.
1.title: Frederick Barnes

1.label: 1x08. General Ludd
1.plot: Liz and the FBI go after an anti-capitalist cabal that's intent on bringing the U.S. economy to its knees.
1.title: General Ludd

1.label: 1x09. Anslo Garrick (1)
1.plot: An assassination attempt on Red brings the FBI under siege.
1.title: Anslo Garrick (1)

1.label: 1x10. Anslo Garrick (2)
1.plot: Liz and a mysterious stranger fight to save Red and Ressler.
1.title: Anslo Garrick (2)

1.label: 1x11. The Good Samaritan
1.plot: A serial killer from Liz's past strikes again while Red hunts for his betrayer.
1.title: The Good Samaritan

1.label: 1x12. The Alchemist
1.plot: The FBI's next target protects the guilty by preying on the DNA of the innocent.
1.title: The Alchemist

1.label: 1x13. The Cyprus Agency
1.plot: On the eve of Liz's adoption, Red puts her on the trail of an adoption agency gone evil.
1.title: The Cyprus Agency

1.label: 1x14. Madeline Pratt
1.plot: A femme fatale from Red's past leads the FBI on a snipe hunt.
1.title: Madeline Pratt

1.label: 1x15. The Judge
1.plot: The FBI pursues a Blacklister who metes out "justice" for those who are wrongly imprisoned.
1.title: The Judge

1.label: 1x16. Mako Tanida
1.plot: As a Yakuza crime lord seeks deadly revenge on Ressler Tom and Jolene face off.
1.title: Mako Tanida

1.label: 1x17. Ivan
1.plot: While chasing a cyber-terrorist, Liz investigates Jolene's disappearance.
1.title: Ivan

1.label: 1x18. Milton Bobbit
1.plot: While working with Red to find Tom's true identity, Liz searches for The Undertaker, a claims adjuster who convinces ordinary people to become contract
1.title: Milton Bobbit

1.label: 1x19. The Pavlovich Brothers
1.plot: While the FBI searches for a Serbian family of kidnappers, Red uses them in a scheme to out Tom, leading to a fateful confrontation with Liz.
1.title: The Pavlovich Brothers

1.label: 1x20. The Kingmaker
1.plot: As the FBI pursues a political fixer known as The Kingmaker, Red seeks Fitch's protection against an unknown enemy who's trying to take him down.
1.title: The Kingmaker

1.label: 1x21. Berlin (1)
1.plot: After discovering the truth behind her father's death, Liz refuses to work with Red, just as his situation grows desperate.
1.title: Berlin (1)

1.label: 1x22. Berlin: Conclusion (2)
1.plot: With the crashing of the mysterious prisoner transport plane, the city is on lock down as the authorities are on the hunt for all the escapees. Meanwhile, with Red  in custody, Liz uses her power to get him out since he is their best chance at finding all the suspects. Elsewhere, their main objective is to track down Berlin, a prisoner on the plane who is somehow involved.
1.title: Berlin: Conclusion (2)

2.label: 2x01. Lord Baltimore
2.plot: While continuing to battle Berlin, Red faces a new threat in the form of Lord Baltimore. A figure from Red's past returns. Liz tries to move on after her showdown with Tom.
2.title: Lord Baltimore

2.label: 2x02. Monarch Douglas Bank
2.plot: A robbery provides Red with an opportunity to take down a questionable bank. Liz questions Red's intentions during the course of her investigation. An impressive addition is made to Cooper's team.
2.title: Monarch Douglas Bank

2.label: 2x03. Dr. James Covington
2.plot: When a body is found missing a heart, Liz and Ressler join forces with Samar Navabi to investigate Dr. Covington's operation. Red and an associate try to take advantage of an opportunity in Indonesia.
2.title: Dr. James Covington

2.label: 2x04. Dr. Linus Creel
2.plot: Red thinks a dangerous sociopsychological experiment may be taking place when several previously nonviolent citizens become killers. Red has a complicated proposition for Naomi and her husband.
2.title: Dr. Linus Creel

2.label: 2x05. The Front
2.plot: The team targets an eco-terrorist cell seeking a deadly weapon. Liz attempts to lose her guardian. Red resorts to manipulation to pursue a special someone.
2.title: The Front

2.label: 2x06. The Mombasa Cartel
2.plot: Liz asks Red for information about deadly wildlife poachers after a mutilated corpse washes ashore. Ressler forms a dangerous habit.
2.title: The Mombasa Cartel

2.label: 2x07. The Scimitar
2.plot: A plot for revenge emerges after an Iranian nuclear scientist is assassinated. Liz and Ressler wind up in a predicament.
2.title: The Scimitar

2.label: 2x08. The Decembrist
2.plot: Red’s motives for Berlin take a sudden turn when he learns Berlin was manipulated by the latest Blacklister to avenge Red. Red and Berlin travel to Moscow to track down a high ranking Russian official who they believe is responsible. Liz struggles to keep her secret from unraveling.
2.title: The Decembrist

2.label: 2x09. Luther Braxton (1)
2.plot: When Red is arrested and taken to a secret detention facility, Liz and the task force set out to save him before he disappears forever. At the facility, Red encounters a thief with whom he shares a complicated history.
2.title: Luther Braxton (1)

2.label: 2x10. Luther Braxton: Conclusion (2)
2.plot: As chaos ensues at the Factory, leaving the fate of Red and the task force unknown, Cooper struggles to rescue his team from the detention facility. It’s a race against time to prevent Luther Braxton attaining confidential information.
2.title: Luther Braxton: Conclusion (2)

2.label: 2x11. Ruslan Denisov
2.plot: When an undercover CIA agent is kidnapped by a band of separatists in Uzbekistan, the task force sets a rescue mission in motion. Red informs Liz and Ressler that they are up against a very dangerous former associate.
2.title: Ruslan Denisov

2.label: 2x12. The Kenyon Family
2.plot: When Red tips Liz off about the disappearance of a polygamous cult leader with dangerous shipping containers buried on his property, the task force sets out to investigate. Red utilizes his sources to appease Fitch’s last words and tries to track down his hidden safe.
2.title: The Kenyon Family

2.label: 2x13. The Deer Hunter
2.plot: Red helps Liz and the task force find a killer — the Deer Hunter — who tracks victims like prey. Meanwhile, the local DC police suspect the city Harbormaster was murdered as Liz struggles to keep her secret from unraveling.
2.title: The Deer Hunter

2.label: 2x14. T. Earl King VI
2.plot: A former paramour involves Reddington in a deadly game with a wealthy, powerful family dynasty whose ill-begotten fortune was amassed from an underground auction of human and material contraband. Meanwhile, Tom takes on a new mission.
2.title: T. Earl King VI

2.label: 2x15. The Major
2.plot: When Agent Keen is questioned in court as a suspect in the murder of the DC Harbormaster, her unusual relationship with Red and their task force falls under scrutiny. Meanwhile, Red enlists Cooper and Ressler to locate "The Major," a dangerous former associate who is key in keeping Liz out of prison.
2.title: The Major

2.label: 2x16. Tom Keen
2.plot: As evidence mounts against Liz in the case of the murdered DC Harbormaster, a federal judge makes it clear to her that she will face severe criminal charges. Reddington and Ressler jump into high gear to exonerate Liz but the only solution is to find the recently vanished Tom Keen — wherever he may be operating in world.
2.title: Tom Keen

2.label: 2x17. The Longevity Initiative
2.plot: The task force tracks a scientist who abducts disabled patients to conduct experiments on immortality. Now back in Washington, DC, Tom scrambles to save himself from new enemies.
2.title: The Longevity Initiative

2.label: 2x18. Vanessa Cruz
2.plot: The task force tracks a provocative female Blacklister, a frame-up artist who targets the wealthy elite. Tom pleads for Liz's help. Red pressures Liz for the Fulcrum, claiming it's now a matter of life and death.
2.title: Vanessa Cruz
